https://www.linkedin.com/in/bobbrowning/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Bob Browning</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Basic functions</strong>:</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/list\\\">Listing files</a>, (tables or collections)* with a powerful filtering capability</li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/detail\\\">Listing individual records</a>&nbsp; (row or document)* with a summary of linked records.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/edit\\\">Create, update an delete</a>&nbsp;data.</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This version supports several relational systems (MySQL. PostgreSQL, SQLite3)&nbsp; plus the MongoDB document database. So it can deal with&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/structured\\\">normalised and denormalized models</a>; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/structured\\\">tabular or structured data</a>. Other databaae management systems can be added.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This test database is running on SQLite3,</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\\"button\\\"><a href=\\\"http://sudsjs.com/page/list\\\">Please take the tour</a></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<hr />\\r\\n<p>* Terminology differs between relational and document&nbsp;database systems. So I have reverted to &#39;classic&#39; terminology:</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<table border=\\\"1\\\" cellpadding=\\\"5\\\" cellspacing=\\\"1\\\">\\r\\n\\t<thead>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<th scope=\\\"col\\\">Classic</th>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<th scope=\\\"col\\\">Relational</th>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<th scope=\\\"col\\\">Document</th>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t</thead>\\r\\n\\t<tbody>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>file</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>table</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>collection</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>record</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>row</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>document</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>field</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>column</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>field</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t</tbody>\\r\\n</table